    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect return value in EmmRegistered for unimplemented procedures\n\n### Summary\nThe `EmmRegistered()` function in the EMM state machine was incorrectly returning `RETURNerror` when processing valid but unimplemented EMM registration events (`_EMMREG_TAU_REQ` and `_EMMREG_SERVICE_REQ`). This caused the state machine to incorrectly report errors for legitimate events.\n\nThis fix ensures that valid events are properly acknowledged with `RETURNok` even when the specific procedures are not yet implemented.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmRegistered.c`: Added `rc = RETURNok;` for `_EMMREG_TAU_REQ` and `_EMMREG_SERVICE_REQ` cases to properly handle valid but unimplemented procedures.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Trigger a Tracking Area Update request or Service Request in EMM_REGISTERED state\n2. Observe that the function returns `RETURNerror` instead of `RETURNok`\n3. This causes incorrect error handling in the upper layers of the EMM state machine\n\nThe fix ensures that these valid events are processed correctly without triggering error paths in the state machine.\n"
}